MiganCore Alembic Migrations
============================

Overview
--------
This directory contains the Alembic migration chain for MiganCore.
All schema changes MUST go through Alembic â€” no manual SQL patches in production.

Migration Chain
---------------
001_baseline          â†’ Full schema from init.sql (embedded)
002_hafidz_ledger     â†’ hafidz_contributions table + view
003_patches           â†’ refresh_tokens, audit_events, api_keys, RLS for memory
004_brain_segments    â†’ brain_segments table
005_feedback_enhance  â†’ interactions_feedback.comment + preference_pair_id FK
006_owner_datasets    â†’ owner_datasets table
007_schema_hardening  â†’ tools.risk_level/policy/max_calls, tenant quotas,
                        auth_lookup_user_by_email(), RLS policy fixes,
                        FORCE RLS, tool seed updates (write_file, generate_image)

Schema Drift (Resolved)
-----------------------
As of 007_schema_hardening the following drift items are closed:
  â€¢ tools.risk_level, tools.policy, tools.max_calls_per_day
  â€¢ tenants.messages_today, tenants.messages_day_reset
  â€¢ Missing RLS policies: interactions_feedback, tools, agent_tool_grants
  â€¢ RLS fail-closed: NULLIF handling on all policies
  â€¢ FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY on all isolated tables
  â€¢ auth_lookup_user_by_email() SECURITY DEFINER for login
  â€¢ write_file and generate_image tools seeded

Running Migrations
------------------
Local Docker (test):
    docker compose -f docker-compose.test.yml up --build api_test --abort-on-container-exit

Production:
    cd /opt/ado/api && alembic upgrade head

Creating a New Revision
-----------------------
    cd api && alembic revision -m "description"

Autogenerate (use with care â€” always review generated SQL):
    cd api && alembic revision --autogenerate -m "description"
